I've played several classes enough that I felt I had a &quot;feel&quot; for them. (I have a 60 paladin, 56 cleric, 51 druid, 41 bard, &amp; 19 mage). With the exception of the bard, the paladin has the most &quot;to do&quot; during a fight. You could practically macro what I do with my other classes during combat. Cleric? med-heal-med-heal-med <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  sometimes stun or if mana is coming out your ears, nuke. Druid? dot-snare-med-med-heal-nuke-med.  Mage? buff pet, /pet attack, nuke at the end.  The warrior, rogue, and monk alts I have made-- well, I've tried all those classes more than once, but I can't really speak about them, because they bored me too much to get them above level 10.  <p><font size="+1">	
