<br>
Not the main tank and assigned to protecting the casters? Very easy to do for a paladins. But for a warrior, he has to be on his toes, because every second is vital, and he'd probably have to quickly switch weapons. Paladins have a bit more room for error, since they can root and stun (no weapon swapping necessary).<br>
<br>
The things a paladin is supposed to do, she can typically do easier than other classes. Breaking root is a good example. Paladins can do this very well just using the spells they probably already have memorized. I've lost count of how many times my enchanter has had to quickly mem new spells because of suprises popping up in a fight.<br>
<br>
To top it off, Paladin's spells are mostly instant gratification. Not holding agro or getting hit too much? Step up, or back down on spell casting and taunting. Friend getting pounded? Chain heal him, no two step necromancer or costly enchanter heals. Paladins are versatile, I agree completely, but it's because we can get a lot of mileage out of two or three spell lines.<br>
